Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This evening, the ministerial committee appointed 
by the cabinet earlier today issued the letter of appointment to 
the state commission of inquiry which will investigate the 
massacre in Hebron and reach conclusions about the facts and 
circumstances pertaining to it. The commission, whose 
composition will be decided by the president of the Supreme 
Court, will be entitled to submit conclusions to the government. 
No time limit has been set for the duration of the commission's 
work. 

